# Sprint 0 Architecture Decisions

## Supabase Client Split

Browser and server Supabase clients are separated into two files:

- supabase-browser.ts — uses createBrowserClient() for client components
- supabase-server.ts — uses createServerClient() + cookies() for server components

This prevents next/headers (server-only) from leaking into client bundles.

## Auth Strategy

- Google OAuth via Supabase Auth redirect flow
- Guest Mode via Supabase anonymous auth (signInAnonymously)
- AuthContext (React Context) for global auth state
- AuthGuard (client component) for route protection
- Server-side redirect in root page for initial auth check

## Profiles Table

A public profiles table linked to auth.users via FK. A database trigger
auto-creates a profile row on user signup (Google or anonymous).

